Riverside Park: Three views photographed in a northwestward direction across the Hudson River towards the Palisades of New Jersey. The vantage point is near West 108th Street.

June 7, 1921.

Walter L. Bogert.

Riverside Park: Three views across the Hudson River from a point in the Park near Columbia University's boathouse (foot of West 115th Street) and which appears in the center of views 1 and 3. No. 2 shows a U.S. Navy destroyer at anchor amid-stream; one of the flotilla's units on its periodical visits to New York.

179-193 East 115th Street, north side, west of, adjoining, and at the N.W. corner of Third Avenue. Nos. 179-189 are two-story frame houses.

1932.

J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York, Negative No. 526

Third Ave., west side, north from East 115th Street. Note the station of the Third Ave. Elevated Line at 116th Street.

June 11, 1936.

W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.

Third Ave., west side, north from (No. 2108) a point slightly north of East 115th to 116th Streets and showing an elevated station at the latter point.

June 11, 1936.

W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.

East 115th Street, west from Third Ave. Partially shown on the left is P.S. No. 57, No. 176 East 115th Street, south side, between Third and Lexington Aves. The bridge like structure shown in the background is a part of the elevated road bed of the New York Central Railroad. The vacant lot appearing on the right was formerly the site of six 2-story frame houses that bore Nos. 179 to 189.

June 11, 1936.

W.P.A. Photo.
